# Managed Backend Provider

Apply only when the adopted project uses a managed database, authentication, storage, or serverless provider.

## Configuration

- Store public client configuration in approved environment variables.
- Store privileged keys only in trusted server or deployment secret stores.
- Commit an example environment file containing placeholders only.
- Never place real project URLs, keys, IDs, or passwords in reusable reference files.

## Authorization

- Enforce access in the provider or trusted backend.
- Treat frontend role checks as user experience only.
- Default to least privilege.
- Test unauthenticated, unauthorized, and cross-tenant access.

## Data Access

- Keep provider queries behind service or repository boundaries.
- Generate or maintain types when supported.
- Use migrations for schema and policy changes.
- Verify policy behavior with representative roles.

## Provider-Specific Guidance

Document selected products, commands, policy models, and deployment steps in the approved project baseline, not in this generic rule.
